})();</script><style> .page-default-page .nav-default-page { border-bottom-color: #f56727; } </style></head><body class="page-default-page"><div class="site-wrapper"><!--[if lt IE 8 ]><section class="info-bar align-center"><p>To use this website properly, please, use a more recent version of Internet Explorer.</p></section><![endif]--><header><h1><a href="./">HTML<sup>5</sup> Shopping Cart</a></h1><ul><li><a href="http://wemakesites.net/" target="_blank">About</a></li><li><a href="https://twitter.com/wemakesitesnet" target="_blank">@wemakesitesnet</a></li><li><a href="http://acidmartin.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Blog</a></li><li><a href="http://wemakesites.net/#!/contact" target="_blank">Contact</a></li></ul></header><nav><ul><li><a href="./" class="nav-default-page">Home</a></li><li><a href="features.html" class="nav-features">Features</a></li><li><a href="download.html" class="nav-download">Download</a></li><li><a href="licensing.html" class="nav-licensing">Licensing</a></li><li><a href="demo.html" class="nav-demo">Demo</a></li><li><a href="purchase.html" class="nav-purchase">Purchase</a></li><li><a href="documentation.html" class="nav-documentation">API</a></li></ul><div class="checkout-placeholder"><div class="acidjs-shopping-cart-dropdown"><!-- / --></div></div></nav><div class="site-content"><noscript>This website as well as HTML5 Cart make heavy use of JavaScript, which is disabled in your browser. For complete experience, please, enable JavaScript and reload the page.</noscript><section class="about"><h2><strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> is an elegant, platform-independent, powerful, <a href="features.html">feature-complete</a> and fully customizable shopping cart solution with easy to use <a href="documentation.html">API</a>, amazing <a href="editor.html">tools</a> and coded entirely in <a href="documentation.html">HTML5</a>, <a href="documentation.html">JavaScript</a> and <a href="documentation.html">CSS3</a>.</h2></section><section><h2>Try out the Demo</h2><p>Select quantity and click to add dummy items to the cart. Once added, you can click the shopping cart icon next to the menu items on top to modify the basket and proceed to the checkout.</p><section class="info-bar"><p>This is a demo of the HTML5 Shopping Cart without a <a href="documentation.html#heading-payment-providers">payment provider</a>. Navigate to <a href="purchase.html">this page</a> if you wish to purchase a license for the component (all our commercial licenses include payment providers). Click <a href="demo-cart-mode.html">here to check</a> the <strong>cart</strong> mode with <strong>add to cart</strong> buttons implementation of HTML5 Cart or <a href="demo-different-items-data-file.html">here to check</a> HTML5 Cart working with a different <a href="documentation.html#cart-items-data-files">items data file</a>.</p></section></section><section><div class="acidjs-shopping-cart"><!-- / --></div></section><section class="features-list"><h2>Features</h2><ul><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-independent">Platform-independent</h3><p><strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> operates fully in the browser, and does not depend on the type of the web-server you are using.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-elegant">Lightweight and Elegant</h3><p>The entire <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> (CSS, JavaScript and template files) is just about 40KB minified and g-zipped.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-payment-gateway">Support for Different Payment Gateways</h3><p>Currently, the small business and enterprise <a href="licensing.html">licenses</a> come with one payment provider - PayPal, but we are working on support for Google Checkout and Amazon Payments. The basic version of <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> does not include a payment provider, but you can easily create one, using our API, which allows the integration of any payment provider. For more information about payment providers, please, check our <a href="documentation.html#heading-payment-providers">Documentation and API page</a>.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-html5">HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript Driven</h3><p>Amazingly fast and responsive. Built with best practices and latest development trends in mind.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-templates">External Templates</h3><p>If you know HTML and CSS you can easily change the looks and the rendering of <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong>.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-currency">International Currency Support</h3><p><strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> will support any currency, supported by the selected <a href="documentation.html#heading-payment-providers">payment provider</a>. It will also add automatically the currency symbol (if available) along with the currency code.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-licenses">Flexible Licenses</h3><p>We provide flexible and affordable licenses for any businesses. For more information, please, check our <a href="licensing.html">licenses page</a>.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-add-to-cart-buttons">Add to Cart Buttons</h3><p>If you do not want to use the "shop" mode of <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong>, you can associate the items you sell on your website with our <a href="documentation.html#add-to-cart-buttons">add to cart buttons</a>. This can done extremely easy, and any license of <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> is shipped with 5 ready to use add to cart buttons. Moreover, you can easily create your own buttons with CSS.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-configure">Easy to Install, Configure and Run.</h3><p>No data bases and server setup - just pure client-side implementation. Basically, what you need to do is adding a few JavaScript and CSS files, defining a few configuration properties and include your items to a simple JSON file. Please, check the <a href="documentation.html">documentation</a> for a jump start using <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong>.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-modes">Modes</h3><p><strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> supports two operation modes - <code>"cart"</code> (default) and <code>"shop"</code>. Please, check our <a href="documentation.html#configuring-html5-cart">documentation</a> page for more info about modes.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-lang">Localizable</h3><p>The current version of <strong class="logo">HTML<sup>5</sup> Cart</strong> comes with English and Bulgarian languages, but creating a <a href="documentation.html#heading-localization">language file</a> is a matter of minutes - all you have to do is to edit a simple JSON file.</p><li><li><h3 class="icons-32 icons-themes">Themes</h3><p>The support for themes is currently under development and will be released soon.</p><li></ul></section></div><footer><ul><li>&copy;2013</li><li><a href="http://wemakesites.net/" target="_blank">About</a></li><li><a href="https://twitter.com/wemakesitesnet" target="_blank">@wemakesitesnet</a></li><li><a href="http://acidmartin.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Blog</a></li><li><a href="http://wemakesites.net/#!/contact" target="_blank">Contact</a></li></ul></footer></div><script src="server/load-js.php?files=..%2Flib%2Fjson2%2Fjson2.js"></script><script src="server/load-js.php?files=..%2Flib%2FjQuery%2Fjquery-1.9.1.min.js"></script><script src="server/load-js.php?files=..%2FAcidJs.ShoppingCart%2Fclasses%2FShoppingCart.min.js"></script><script src="server/load-js.php?files=../classes/site.min.js"></script><script> (function() { "use strict"; window.site = new AcidJs.Site({ page: "default-page", debug: false, cartConfig: {"paymentProvider":"ExampleProvider","cartDataFile":"AcidJs.ShoppingCart\/data\/for-dummies.json","mode":"shop","thumbs":{"width":204,"height":264}} }); })(); </script></body></html>